    <p>“Quar­an­tine” – a word lit­tle used in the daily con­text prior to this year – has found its way into the lex­i­con of most peo­ple. It has be­come</p>
    <p>in­ex­tri­ca­bly linked with in­ter­na­tional travel and is now even as­so­ci­ated with one’s po­lit­i­cal choices in some coun­tries. Dif­fer­ent coun­tries have their own take on it – from move­ment con­trol or­ders in Malaysia to to­tal lock­downs in parts of China. A8&9</p>

